<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 8 月 11 日星期五 00:12:30 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[A New Omicron Subvariant, Dubbed ‘Eris,’ Heralds Covid-19’s Resurgence]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>我们对美国最常见的亚变体 EG.5 的了解<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124938"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833284?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">曼哈顿的一个弹出式 Covid-19 测试帐篷。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：《华尔街日报》的加比·琼斯</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124938"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/brianna-abbott" itemprop="url" rel="author">布莱恩娜·阿博特</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jon-kamp" itemprop="url" rel="author">乔恩·坎普</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jared-s-hopkins" itemprop="url" rel="author">贾里德·S·霍普金斯</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 3:18（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eg5-eris-new-covid-19-variant-fa3cc260"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>现在还不要指望 Covid-19 被排除在外。</p><p>随着 Omicron 变种的另一个分支势头强劲，美国的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-19-rates-rising-summer-780ab1d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">Covid-19 感染人数</a>正在上升——在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rsv-influenza-covid-19-tripledemic-this-winter-11667560508?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">呼吸道疾病</a>通常会激增的秋季之前。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/what-do-we-actually-know-about-covid-19-not-enough-ec1dcafe?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">该病毒的持续进化</a>提醒人们，尽管这种疾病的破坏性远不如以前，但 Covid-19 仍然对许多人来说是一个麻烦，对一些人来说仍然是一个<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/long-covid-symptoms-recovery-not-over-2e535790?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">严重的风险</a>。废水中病毒浓度的不断上升和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/face-mask-mandates-fall-away-among-many-hospitals-doctors-6ecaa3e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">医院感染的</a>增加表明，Covid-19 仍然难以预测。</p><p>这种名为 EG.5 的新亚变体是另一个名为 XBB.1.9.2 的变体的后代，据世界卫生组织称，自 8 月 7 日以来，至少有 51 个国家报告了该变体，该组织将 EG.5 归类为本周感兴趣的一个变体。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833823?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> X（以前称为 Twitter）上的一些科学家将其非正式地称为“Eris”。世界卫生组织表示，与其他 Omicron 亚变体一样，EG.5 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/omicrons-trajectory-shows-challenge-of-maintaining-immune-defenses-11651829400?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">具有免疫逃逸特性</a>，但没有迹象表明它更严重。</p><p>据美国疾病控制与预防中心称，截至 8 月 5 日，EG.5 预计约占美国病例的 17%，使其成为美国最流行的病毒版本。它是由十多个 Omicron 分支组成的动物园之一，估计至少占病例的 1%。</p><p>路易斯安那州卫生官员兼路易斯安那州卫生部医疗主任约瑟夫·坎特博士表示，由于没有足够的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cdc-director-rochelle-walensky-politicization-science-9c291c7e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">检测和测序数据</a>，疾病预防控制中心无法再对美国每个地区进行变异预测。</p><p> “我们预计 EG.5 将继续发挥重要作用，”坎特说。</p><p>卫生官员、疫苗制造商和医生正在为秋季疫苗接种活动做准备，这次活动将与之前的活动有所不同：疫苗将通过<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-plans-for-end-of-covid-19-shot-treatment-coverage-11660838418?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">商业市场</a>而不是政府购买分发给药房和医生办公室。这些疫苗针对的是最近占主导地位的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/next-covid-shots-in-the-u-s-will-target-omicron-offshoot-xbb-1-5-35e212a0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">XBB.1.5 菌株，</a>符合美国食品和药物管理局今年早些时候制定的指示。</p><p>坎特说，针对 XBB.1.5 更新的助推器应该保留针对 EG.5 的良好保护，因为 Omicron 子变体是相似的。他说，很难预测这种保护会持续多久。</p><p>辉瑞<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pfizers-covid-boost-crashes-to-earth-51e1d0?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">首席执行官艾伯特·布尔拉 (Albert Bourla)</a>本月表示，<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PFE" class="company-name">辉瑞</a>预计其新疫苗将于本月获得批准，疫苗接种可能于 9 月开始。辉瑞公司发言人表示，预计该增强剂能够对抗 EG.5，因为它是 Omicron 的一个分支，但正在进行实验室测试以确保这一点。辉瑞和合作伙伴<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BNTX" class="company-name">BioNTech</a>在 6 月份的会议上向 FDA 顾问介绍了如何更新疫苗的动物测试。</p><p> FDA 不太可能要求制造商生产针对 EG.5 的疫苗，因为供应无法及时准备好以供秋季活动使用。辉瑞和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MRNA" class="company-name">Moderna</a>至少需要三个月的时间才能针对 Covid-19 进行 mRNA 注射。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>发言人表示，Moderna 的更新疫苗供应充足，正在等待 FDA 批准分配剂量。他说，初步测试表明该镜头对 EG.5 有效，更多测试正在进行中。</p><p>一位发言人表示<span class="company-name-type">，</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NVAX" class="">Novavax</a>的 Covid-19 疫苗使用了不同的技术，该公司正在向监管机构提交数据以授权其加强剂，并预计在 9 月份获得许可并发货。</p><p>是否立即接受加强注射或等待新的加强注射<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/think-you-never-got-covid-19-thank-your-genes-d61c7507?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">取决于某人的健康状况和风险</a>， <strong>&nbsp;</strong>威尔康奈尔医学院微生物学和免疫学教授约翰摩尔博士说。他说，患有已有疾病或免疫系统受损的人以及未接种疫苗的人仍然面临高风险。</p><p> “如果您和您的医生认为您现在需要加强注射，请立即注射，”摩尔说。 “这非常有个性。没有一个简单的桶可以容纳每个美国人。”</p><p>去年，RSV 早期严重激增以及流感导致<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/rsv-hospitalizations-babies-young-children-11668080478?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">儿科医院不堪重负</a>，卫生官员正在为其他呼吸道感染的增加做好准备。 FDA 已<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/next-vaccine-you-should-get-health-advisers-may-recommend-rsv-shots-60849622?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">批准首款</a><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-pfizer-rsv-vaccine-rolls-out-into-headwinds-of-hesitancy-74c8aece?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">用于 60 岁及以上成年人的</a>RSV 疫苗以及一种<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/fda-approves-first-rsv-drug-to-protect-all-infants-from-virus-52907caf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">用于保护婴儿的新药</a>。</p><p> “我们正在进入一个我们并不真正知道这些病毒将如何相互作用的季节，”康涅狄格州公共卫生部专员马尼沙·朱萨尼博士说。</p><p>美国不再像以前那样密切跟踪 Covid-19 感染和住院情况。长期以来，感染情况一直难以记录，因为人们不再在向州卫生当局提供数据的设施中接受检测。医院还取消了对所有患者的常规检测。</p><p>几周来，医院内的 Covid-19 病例一直呈上升趋势。 CDC 表示，截至 7 月底的最新一周内，有 9,056 人因 Covid-19 入院，增长了 12.5%。许多患者因其他原因住院，而不是因为感染，但医院的阳性检测可以反映出社区感染流行率的增加。</p><p> Covid-19 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/one-million-deaths-the-hole-the-pandemic-made-in-u-s-society-11643662159?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">每天都会导致新的死亡病例</a>，尽管<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/why-the-u-s-covid-19-death-toll-is-still-rising-93b2b12a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">远未达到大流行初期的峰值</a>。最近的死亡证明数据显示，美国平均每天有不到 100 例 Covid-19 死亡病例。 2021 年 1 月，一周内每天死亡人数达到历史最高值约 3,700 人。</p><p>写信给 Brianna Abbott（ <a href="mailto:brianna.abbott@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">brianna.abbott@wsj.com</a> ）、Jon Kamp（ <a href="mailto:Jon.Kamp@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Jon.Kamp@wsj.com</a> ）和 Jared S. Hopkins（ <a href="mailto:jared.hopkins@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jared.hopkins@wsj.com</a> ）</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:18:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/eg5-eris-new-covid-19-variant-fa3cc260</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/eg5-eris-new-covid-19-variant-fa3cc260<author><![CDATA[Brianna AbbottJon KampJared S. Hopkins]]></author><category>华尔街日报健康</category><category>药品</category><category>疫苗</category><category>医疗保健/生命科学</category><category>特殊药物/药物</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>免疫接种</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>医疗/程序</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>健康</category><category>免疫接种</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>医疗</category><category>程序</category><category>药品</category><category>疫苗</category><category>卫生保健</category><category>生命科学</category><category>专门药物</category><category>药物</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Iran Releases Four Americans From Evin Prison]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>德黑兰寻求冻结韩国70亿美元能源收入<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001125422"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="563" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833471?width=860&amp;height=563" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2016 年 2 月发布的一张未注明日期的照片中，美国人 Siamak Namazi。他于 2015 年前往伊朗出差时被捕。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：讲义/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001125422"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/vivian-salama" itemprop="url" rel="author">维维安·萨拉马</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 3:15（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——经过拜登政府、白宫和家属律师<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-launches-quiet-diplomatic-push-with-iran-to-cool-tensions-2f45af3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">长达数月的外交推动，</a>伊朗于周四释放了四名被监禁的美国人，并将他们软禁起来，打算允许他们在未来几周内前往美国说。</p><p>一位知情人士称，第五名美国人已经被软禁，下个月将被允许与其他四人一起离开伊朗。</p><p>白宫国家安全委员会表示：“在他们全部返回美国之前，我们不会休息。”</p><p>伊朗驻联合国代表团发言人表示，两国已同意“相互释放并赦免五名囚犯”。</p><p> “将这些囚犯移出监狱标志着执行该协议的重要第一步，”发言人说。</p><p>知情人士称，不会释放在美国关押的囚犯来换取美国人，伊朗也不会获得任何可用于受制裁贸易的资金。</p><p>德黑兰寻求从因美国制裁而困在国外的伊朗能源收入中获取数十亿美元，以换取释放囚犯和限制其核计划。在特朗普政府加强对伊朗石油出口的制裁后，伊朗官员将目光投向韩国持有的 70 亿美元，并要求获得在伊拉克持有的数十亿美元用于交付天然气和石油。</p><p>知情人士表示，有关释放资金的讨论仍在进行中，但结果尚未确定。美国财政部正在探索如何将这些资金从无法使用的首尔受限账户转移到第三国，以便用于人道主义目的和美国制裁允许的其他贸易。</p><p>周四，其中一名人质<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09#phrase-person?ref=PERSON%7CNamazi%2C%20Siamak;onlineSignificance=prominent" class="icon none">Siamak Namazi</a>的家人收到直接视觉确认，Namazi、Emad Shargi 和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09#phrase-person?ref=PERSON%7CTahbaz%2C%20Morad;onlineSignificance=prominent" class="icon none">Morad Tahbaz</a>已从监狱获释，家人的律师 Jared Genser</p>说。他说，这三名男子和第四名未透露姓名的美国人已被带到监狱办公室，并被告知将被释放。他说，拜登政府周三下午已通知四名人质的家人，这是预料之中的。<p></p><p>自1979年伊斯兰革命后不久华盛顿和德黑兰断绝关系以来，瑞士一直代表美国在伊朗的外交利益，瑞士一直参与了谈判。据知情人士透露，瑞士驻德黑兰大使将可以完全接触被软禁的美国人。这位人士表示，卡塔尔和阿曼也协助推动了这些谈判。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="641" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833474?width=639&amp;height=641" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">莫拉德·塔赫巴兹 (Morad Tahbaz) 于 2018 年入狱。</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-grants-furlough-to-american-prisoner-11664669202" target="_blank" class="icon none">纳马齐于 2015 年 10 月在前往伊朗出差时被捕</a>，罪名是与敌对政府合作。环保人士塔巴兹于 2018 年入狱，因间谍罪被判 10 年徒刑，已服刑 5 年。商人沙尔吉于 2018 年被捕，并于 2020 年未经审判以间谍罪被判处 10 年监禁。这三人都是美国和伊朗双重国籍。塔巴兹还拥有英国国籍。</p><p>知情人士称，另外两名被释放的人质，包括一名妇女，要求保密他们的身份。</p><p>最新的外交尝试代表了拜登政府的平衡之举，重点是缓和今年与德黑兰的紧张关系。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-strikes-kill-six-in-ukraine-as-moscow-looks-to-undermine-kyivs-counteroffensive-177b0c2d" target="_blank" class="icon none">伊朗为俄罗斯在乌克兰的战争提供了无人机</a>，推进<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-expands-nuclear-program-as-talks-to-revive-2015-deal-falter-11662569582" target="_blank" class="icon none">铀浓缩活动</a>，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-tried-to-seize-two-oil-tankers-near-strait-of-hormuz-u-s-navy-says-4be301e1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">在波斯湾扣押了油轮</a>。</p><p>官员们表示，在解放美国人的努力的同时，继续就恢复国际核协议进行谈判，该协议限制伊朗的核计划，以换取取消经济制裁。美国在前总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普的</a>领导下退出了该协议。</p><p>随着总统选举的临近，拜登政府迫切希望避免将与伊朗的谈判推上政治议程的首位。然而，美国政府也指出，鉴于伊朗的铀浓缩活动以及所谓的整个地区的破坏稳定活动，谈判有可能失败。</p><p>这些会谈也是在紧张的地区环境下进行的，美国正在向中东增派部队，以阻止和威慑霍尔木兹海峡针对国际商业油轮的袭击。美国还多次谴责和惩罚伊朗在乌克兰战争中向俄罗斯提供的援助。</p><p>写信给 Vivian Salama： <a href="mailto:vivian.salama@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">vivian.salama@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 19:15:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-releases-four-americans-from-evin-prison-b396ee09<author><![CDATA[Vivian Salama]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>缓刑/家庭拘留</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>埃马德·沙吉</category><category>贾里德·根瑟</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>缓刑</category><category>居家拘留</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Maui Wildfires Leave at Least 36 Dead]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>飓风引发的大火摧毁了历史名镇拉海纳<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124181"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=1E4C7220-8609-4F03-A17C-70F3E330A2CD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fhawaii-maui-wildfires-36-dead-6e07f2b7&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">官员称，飓风引发的野火席卷夏威夷毛伊岛，已造成至少 36 人死亡。卫星图像显示了热门​​旅游小镇拉海纳的破坏规模。照片：Matthew Thayer/毛伊岛新闻/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124181"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/alicia-caldwell" itemprop="url" rel="author">艾丽西亚·A·考德威尔</a></span>、 <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jennifer-calfas" itemprop="url" rel="author">詹妮弗·卡尔法斯</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/michael-wright" itemprop="url" rel="author">迈克尔·赖特</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 1:52（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hawaii-maui-wildfires-36-dead-6e07f2b7"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>夏威夷卡胡卢伊——当局称<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/hawaii-wildfires-maui-big-island-lahaina-hurricane-dora-evacuations-800bf315?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，席卷毛伊岛、摧毁历史名城拉海纳的野火</a>已造成至少 36 人死亡。</p><p>本周早些时候在夏威夷岛上爆发的三场野火是由数百英里外飓风多拉的风力助长的。野火的原因尚未确定。</p><p>拉海纳有超过 271 座建筑遭到损坏或毁坏。拉海纳是夏威夷王国历史悠久的前首都，位于毛伊岛西海岸，现已成为热门旅游目的地。毛伊岛内陆地区（包括哈雷阿卡拉国家公园）至少 1,000 英亩的土地已被烧焦。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833197?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三，毛伊岛拉海纳市海滨的建筑物、树木和船只被野火摧毁。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：梅森·贾维/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>据联邦紧急事务管理局称，毛伊岛西部约有 11,000 人断电，手机和固定电话服务也已中断。毛伊县官员表示，周三晚间没有针对三场火灾发布新的疏散命令或遏制估计。</p><p> FEMA 表示，截至周四上午，毛伊岛的 6 个避难所已容纳 2000 多人。其中一个避难所位于毛伊岛高中，疏散人员睡在地板上的垫子上。其他人则选择睡在学校停车场的车里。</p><p>周三，伊夫·赫卢 (Yves Helou) 和亚里娜·扬查克 (Yaryna Yanchak) 在拉海纳郊外的酒店缺乏食物和水后，在毛伊岛高中过夜。</p><p>他们表示，由于没有手机服务，他们最初并不知道席卷拉海纳和附近社区的大规模野火。两人说，酒店工作人员只告诉他们，高速公路附近发生了灌木丛火灾。</p><p> “我们是无意中来到这里的，”来自芝加哥的 31 岁的 Helou 说。 “我们只是出去寻找食物。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web,mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>由于道路封闭，他们无法进入度假村，他们的行李和扬查克的护照已经回到度假村，两人还无法安排离开毛伊岛。他们希望周四晚些时候离开。</p><p>在联邦团队的支持下，毛伊岛的搜救工作正在进行，8,250 人已被命令撤离该岛。直升机一直在拉海纳上空喷水以控制火势。州和县当局敦促游客远离或离开。夏威夷交通部部长埃德·斯尼芬 (Ed Sniffen) 表示，周三有超过 11,000 名旅客以及约 400 名航空公司工作人员离开毛伊岛。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833199?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三晚上，毛伊岛的卡胡卢伊机场挤满了人，数千人试图离开该岛。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：里克·鲍默/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>周三晚上，毛伊岛的卡胡卢伊机场挤满了人，数千人试图离开该岛。有些人睡在航站楼里。夏威夷航空运营从机场飞往檀香山的深夜航班，帮助人们撤离该岛。周四，该航空公司增加了 4 趟航班，并提供从毛伊岛出发的 19 美元折扣机票，以帮助紧急离开的人们。</p><p>亚当·温特劳布 (Adam Weintraub) 表示，救援队评估烧毁地区时可能会造成更多人员伤亡。</p>周四，夏威夷紧急事务管理局发言人在“早安美国”节目中。<p></p><p> “我们希望得到最好的结果，但我们也做好了最坏的准备，”他说。</p><p>海岸警卫队表示，已救出14名逃入大海躲避烟雾和火焰的人。</p><p>拜登总统周四宣布夏威夷发生重大灾难，并批准了州长协助应对和恢复工作的请求。州长乔什·格林说，该声明还包括为毛伊县居民寻求临时住房和房屋维修提供资金。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="935" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833115?width=1260&amp;height=935" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">夏威夷毛伊岛拉海纳地区 Banyan Court 山火的卫星图像。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Maxar Technologies </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="935" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833114?width=1260&amp;height=935" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">野火袭击前的同一地区。在彩色红外卫星图像中，烧毁的区域显示为黑色和灰色，而健康的植被显示为红色阴影。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Maxar Technologies</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “我保证不遗余力地扑灭破坏性的野火，为流离失所者提供庇护，治疗和安慰受创伤的人，支持我们的急救人员，恢复通讯线路，并争取我们联邦和县合作伙伴的援助，以应对这一历史性的灾难。”一生的灾难，”格林说。</p><p>今年夏天，野火和其他形式的极端天气席卷了世界多个地区。大火席卷了希腊、葡萄牙和加拿大，而中国则面临着严重的洪水和灼热的热浪。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/july-2023-hottest-month-record-climate-change-5e5b3097?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">七月是世界上有记录以来最热的月份</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="672" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/ce8ee128-0322-47e6-8c1b-480d6a6040aa-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>拉海纳各地闷烧瓦砾的视频片段显示了破坏的规模。建筑物、棕榈树和汽车被火焰吞没，风吹过的火墙和烟雾蔓延到整个城镇。受灾地区包括前街，这​​是一条深受游客欢迎的不拘一格的道路，两旁遍布商店、企业和历史建筑。</p><p> 1800 年代中期，水手和船只停泊在历史悠久的捕鲸小镇拉海纳。其历史街区是国家历史名胜名录的一部分。据拉海纳修复基金会称，鲍德温故居博物馆是拉海纳的地标，是毛伊岛最古老的房屋。一棵树龄 150 年的巨大榕树是拉海纳市中心的中心景观，于 1873 年被带到岛上。据该镇网站称，这棵树在火灾中受损。</p><p>副州长西尔维娅·卢克周三发布紧急公告，鼓励暂停飞往毛伊岛的所有非必要航空旅行。格林出差归来期间，卢克担任代理州长，他启动了夏威夷国民警卫队以帮助应对工作。</p><p> “我们正在不懈努力，确保每个受影响者的健康和安全，”卢克在参加对损失的空中评估后在周三晚间发表的一份声明中表示。 “虽然我们深爱的拉海纳已经永远改变，但社区的爱和阿罗哈是坚定不移的。”</p><p>周三，夏威夷大岛也发生了三场野火，但当局没有报告任何人死亡。周三晚上，夏威夷县官员取消了与火灾有关的所有强制疏散。</p><p>当局表示，他们已为周二飓风多拉的到来做好准备，但尚未为随后发生的野火做好准备。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833195?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">视频片段显示，拉海纳的建筑物、棕榈树和汽车被大火吞没。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：JEFF MELICHAR/TMX/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>夏威夷国防部副将肯尼思·哈拉少将表示，长期干燥、低湿度和大风助长了野火。</p><p>毛伊岛是夏威夷第二大旅游岛屿，仅次于欧胡岛。根据该州商业、经济发展和旅游部的数据，毛伊岛今年上半年接待游客近 150 万人次，较 2022 年同期增长 5.7%。同期游客总支出为 34.7 亿美元，比去年增长约 25%。</p><p> “这将是一条漫长的复苏之路，”卢克在新闻发布会上说。 “我们对毛伊岛发生的悲剧深感悲痛，尤其是那些失去家人和朋友的人。”</p><p>哈拉指示那些想要寻找亲人的人前往毛伊岛紧急事务管理局。</p><p> — <em>Allison Pohle 对本文做出了贡献。</em></p><p>写信给 Alicia A. Caldwell ( <a href="mailto:alicia.caldwell@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">alicia.caldwell@wsj.com</a> )、Michael Wright ( <a href="mailto:michael.wright@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">michael.wright@wsj.com</a> ) 和 Jennifer Calfas ( <a href="mailto:jennifer.calfas@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jennifer.calfas@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:52:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hawaii-maui-wildfires-36-dead-6e07f2b7</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/hawaii-maui-wildfires-36-dead-6e07f2b7<author><![CDATA[Alicia A. CaldwellJennifer CalfasMichael Wright]]></author><category> WSJSpeeddesk</category><category>野火</category><category>野火</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>灾害/事故</category><category>飓风/台风</category><category>风暴</category><category>生活/生活方式</category><category>自然灾害</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>天气</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>灾难</category><category>事故</category><category>飓风</category><category>台风</category><category>风暴</category><category>活的</category><category>生活方式</category><category>自然灾害</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>天气</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ecuador Declares State of Emergency After Presidential Hopeful Killed]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>总统吉列尔莫·拉索表示，安第斯国家正努力应对日益严重的贩毒团伙暴力事件，8月20日的选举将继续进行<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124585"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=3A297452-49E9-4885-AD64-0A664604940D&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fecuador-declares-state-of-emergency-after-presidential-candidate-killed-6e639e72&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">距离大选不到两周，厄瓜多尔总统候选人费尔南多·维拉维森西奥在离开基多的竞选活动时被枪杀。这位腐败批评者表示，他收到了死亡威胁。照片：Shutterstock<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124585"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/ryan-dube" itemprop="url" rel="author">瑞安·杜贝</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 1:45（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-declares-state-of-emergency-after-presidential-candidate-killed-6e639e72"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>厄瓜多尔总统吉列尔莫·拉索表示，在这个饱受<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/cocaine-trade-and-gang-violence-strike-hard-in-once-peaceful-ecuador-bad953c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">毒品暴力</a>影响的国家，枪手<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-presidential-candidate-who-had-denounced-gangs-is-assassinated-dad61aa5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">杀害了一名总统候选人</a>后，他下令士兵上街加强安全。</p><p>拉索周四宣布全国进入为期 60 天的紧急状态，这也将限制行动自由和集会权等公民自由。周三费尔南多·比亚维森西奥被杀后，其他几位候选人暂停了竞选活动，这是该国首次出现总统候选人被暗杀的情况。</p><p>拉索还宣布全国哀悼三天，并表示 8 月 20 日的选举将按计划进行。</p><p> “我们不会将权力和民主制度交给有组织犯罪，”拉索在电视评论中说。 “选举不会暂停。”</p><p> 59 岁的前记者兼国会议员比亚维森西奥 (Villavicencio) 在首都基多一所学校参加竞选活动后被杀。袭击发生在晚间高峰时段，地点靠近该市繁忙的金融中心。</p><p>距离投票仅 11 天，在支持者面前发生的枪击事件让厄瓜多尔人感到不安，他们已经在应对暴力犯罪激增的问题。贩毒团伙争夺可卡因贩运路线的控制权，在这个曾经相对和平的国家引发了流血事件。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833230?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三，警方封锁了基多总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥被杀的学校周围地区。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：胡安·迭戈·黑山/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>“一切都那么令人困惑。太混乱了。人们不知道该怎么办。他们哭着，非常害怕。”摄影师迭戈·托雷斯 (Diego Torres) 和妻子在距离学校一个街区的地方散步时，听到了他所说的高威力步枪的射击声。 “这是另一个层面，更高级的犯罪行为。”</p><p>报道厄瓜多尔犯罪浪潮的托雷斯表示，他在枪声停止后赶到了现场。他说警方让他回去，因为他们发现了两枚没有爆炸的手榴弹。拉索说，袭击者在逃跑时投掷了一枚手榴弹，但并未爆炸，以分散当局的注意力。当局尚未透露更多细节。</p><p>总检察长办公室称，六人因与这起谋杀案有关而被捕，一名嫌疑人被捕后因伤重死亡。</p><p>对于枪击事件负责的说法相互矛盾。在 X（该网站以前称为 Twitter）上发布的一段视频中，全副武装的蒙面男子声称自己对这起杀戮负责，他们自称来自厄瓜多尔最大、最暴力的帮派之一“狼群”。后来，另一段视频中，未戴面具的男子也自称是狼队成员，称该团伙并未参与其中。 《华尔街日报》无法证实这些视频的真实性。</p><p>比亚维森西奥最近表示，他收到了另一个名为 Choneros 的团伙的威胁，安全专家称该团伙与墨西哥锡那罗亚贩毒集团有联系。</p><p>人们将比亚维森西奥之死与 1989 年哥伦比亚总统候选人路易斯·卡洛斯·加兰遇刺事件进行比较。</p>在加兰竞选时承诺将毒贩引渡到美国后，加兰被毒枭巴勃罗·埃斯科瓦尔的追随者杀害。哥伦比亚安全官员也参与了加兰的杀戮并被定罪。<p></p><p>周四，这起谋杀案引起了华盛顿和北京的谴责。美国国家安全顾问杰克·沙利文称这是对厄瓜多尔民主的攻击。中国外交部表示，希望厄瓜多尔能够安全举行选举。</p><p>比亚维森西奥的竞选总监安东尼奥·洛佩斯表示，他在这位候选人被杀前几分钟离开了集会。洛佩斯在集会上回忆起比亚维森西奥告诉支持者，他为自己被犯罪分子憎恨而感到自豪，如果当选，他将给帮派 90 天的时间交出武器，然后再追捕他们。洛佩斯说，候选人最后一次收到死亡威胁是在八天前。</p><p>洛佩斯说：“民主被枪杀，反腐败斗争被削弱。” “他最大的斗争是打击毒品政治。”</p><p>最近几周，厄瓜多尔也有其他政客被杀。 7月，一名枪手在港口城市曼塔的市长奥古斯丁·英特里亚戈出席一场公共活动时刺杀了他。国民议会候选人 Rider Sánchez 上个月在沿海城市埃斯梅拉达斯被枪杀。路易斯·乔尼洛 (Luis Chonillo) 是犯罪猖獗的瓜亚基尔郊区的市长，他在五月份上任一天后就遭遇了一次暗杀。</p><p>随着有组织犯罪的猖獗，这场流血事件引发了人们对政治暴力在这个拥有 1800 万人口的安第斯国家蔓延的担忧。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833229?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">总统候选人费尔南多·比亚维森西奥 (Fernando Villavicencio) 在周三被枪杀前几分钟在一所学校的竞选活动中挥舞着国旗。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>华盛顿智库美洲对话组织的高级研究员迈克尔·希夫特表示：“哥伦比亚等其他国家的经验表明，有组织犯罪往往会演变为政治暴力。”</p><p> “当它这样做时，对民主制度和对政治制度的信心的影响可能是毁灭性的，”希夫特说。 “厄瓜多尔的转移速度快得惊人。”</p><p>如今，厄瓜多尔是拉丁美洲最危险的国家之一。据内政部称，自 2019 年以来，凶杀案增加了四倍，去年达到创纪录的 4,800 起，并<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/andes-turmoil-rattles-governments-spurs-migration-to-u-s-d8396753?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">导致移民激增</a>，主要是前往美国。</p><p>警方和安全专家表示， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/colombias-acreage-of-coca-used-to-make-cocaine-surges-to-record-11666306614?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">邻国哥伦比亚创纪录的可卡因产量</a>以及墨西哥和阿尔巴尼亚贩毒集团支持的厄瓜多尔贩毒团伙之间的暴力事件引发了暴力浪潮。</p><p>暴力事件主要发生在瓜亚基尔等沿海城市，帮派争夺通往海港的可卡因贩运路线的控制权。警方和居民称，帮派执法者枪杀检察官和警察，将尸体吊在桥上，并招募儿童进行袭击。</p><p>由于选民要求加强安全，比亚维森西奥承诺打击贩毒团伙和有组织犯罪，他称这些犯罪团伙与厄瓜多尔政治精英关系密切。</p><p>他的政党表示，在曼塔市长被杀后，出于安全考虑，已讨论暂停他的竞选活动。比亚维森西奥的政党表示，他们坚决认为他们应该继续竞选。</p><p>比亚维森西奥当时表示：“当犯罪分子杀害公民和当局时，保持沉默和躲藏是一种懦弱和共谋的行为。” “我批准我的决定，继续进行日常斗争，直到我们击败黑手党。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833232?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">周三，费尔南多·比亚维森西奥在基多遭到枪击后，他的亲属在诊所里等候。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：何塞·雅各姆/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>比亚维森西奥表示，他将在厄瓜多尔亚马逊地区为帮派头目建造一座最高安全级别的监狱，加强与美国的禁毒合作，并让军队负责用于运输可卡因的港口。他还承诺根除政府、警察和司法部门的腐败。</p><p>政治分析人士表示，比亚维森西奥是有机会在 8 月 20 日第一轮投票中获得第二名的候选人之一。民意调查显示，没有人能够在第一轮投票中获得足够的票数彻底赢得总统宝座。这种情况需要在十月份在两位前两名候选人之间进行决选。</p><p>在进入政坛之前，比亚维森西奥以记者身份而闻名，根据对政府腐败的详细调查，特别是在前总统拉斐尔·科雷亚执政期间，撰写了长篇文章和书籍。分析人士称，他的工作帮助科雷亚在 2020 年缺席被判腐败罪。</p><p>居住在比利时的科雷亚对比亚维森西奥的遇害表示哀悼，并向他的家人表示哀悼。</p><p> “厄瓜多尔已经成为一个失败的国家，”科雷亚在 X 上写道，“我对他的家人表示声援。”</p><p> 2014年，在人权组织称科雷亚政府镇压该国新闻自由的过程中，比亚维森西奥被指控诽谤，之后他躲藏在亚马逊地区。比亚维森西奥曾与一个土著部落一起生活过一段时间，后来逃到秘鲁寻求庇护。</p><p> 2017 年科雷亚政府结束后返回厄瓜多尔，比亚维森西奥当选为国民议会议员，并领导监督委员会。</p><p>他继续调查政府腐败，并就中国建造的基础设施项目的问题提出报告。他声称，以石油运输为担保的中国贷款已使该国损失数十亿美元，并助长了腐败。</p><p>美国陆军战争学院战略研究所研究中国与拉丁美洲关系的专家埃文·埃利斯表示，比亚维森西奥关于中国在厄瓜多尔日益增长的影响力的研究影响了他自己对北京在拉丁美洲不断扩大的作用的看法。</p><p> “对我来说，他是一个非常好的人，他情不自禁地说出了他所看到的真相，即使他有时会搬起石头砸自己的脚，树敌，”埃利斯说。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——珍妮·卡罗莱纳·冈萨雷斯对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给 Ryan Dubé： <a href="mailto:ryan.dube@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">ryan.dube@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-declares-state-of-emergency-after-presidential-candidate-killed-6e639e72</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ecuador-declares-state-of-emergency-after-presidential-candidate-killed-6e639e72<author><![CDATA[Ryan Dubé]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>毒品贩运/交易</category><category>帮派</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩运/走私</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>费尔南多·比亚维森西奥</category><category>吉列尔莫·拉索</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>贩毒</category><category>交易</category><category>帮派</category><category>凶杀案</category><category>犯罪企业</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>贩卖</category><category>走私</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[What Is Happening in Niger? What to Know About the Coup]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>美国西非反恐盟友民选总统下台引发军事干预威胁<figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829069/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="军政府政变的支持者在尼日尔首都尼亚美集会。" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption>军政府政变的支持者在尼日尔首都尼亚美集会。法新社/盖蒂图片社<span>法新社/盖蒂图片社</span></figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001107681"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001107681"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/gabriele-steinhauser" itemprop="url" rel="author">加布里埃尔·斯坦豪瑟</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 10 日下午 1:26（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> 7 月 26 日，尼日尔精锐总统卫队官员<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apparent-coup-attempt-hits-u-s-ally-niger-e3efa36d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">拘留了西非国家当选总统</a>穆罕默德·巴祖姆，并宣布自己为该国新领导人。这次政变令美国和欧洲政府感到震惊，这些国家一直<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-us-russia-africa-86cf1454?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与巴祖姆和尼日尔军队密切合作</a>，打击非洲萨赫勒地区的伊斯兰武装分子。</p><p>尼日尔的一些西非邻国（主要<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与美国和欧洲结盟</a>）威胁要使用武力恢复巴祖姆的地位。其他<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/france-prepares-to-evacuate-european-citizens-from-coup-hit-niger-d46774af?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与俄罗斯结盟的</a>国家则表示，他们将捍卫尼日尔的新军政府。</p><h3>美国和欧洲政府为何担心尼日尔政变？</h3><p>尼日尔一直是美国和欧洲<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-builds-new-firewall-to-stop-spread-of-militant-islamists-11670771719?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">打击基地组织和伊斯兰国武装分子</a>的中心，这些武装分子近年来在撒哈拉以南的半干旱地区萨赫勒地区杀害了数千人。在马里和布基纳法索军方领导的政府驱逐了一直在那里与伊斯兰叛乱分子作战的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-embassy-evacuation-africa-33d18bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">法国和其他西方军队</a>后，尼日尔变得更加重要。美国已花费约 5 亿美元武装尼日尔军队，配备从帐篷、收音机到侦察机和装甲运兵车等各种装备。美国在尼日尔驻有约 1,100 名士兵，他们训练当地特种部队并为他们执行任务提供建议。法国在尼日尔驻有大约 1,500 名士兵。</p><p>欧盟还依赖世界上最贫穷国家之一的尼日尔<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/eu-considers-substantial-fund-for-africa-to-deal-with-migrants-1440871414?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">来阻止非洲移民</a>进入利比亚并从那里进入欧盟。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="819" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828956?width=1260&amp;height=819" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">政变支持者在尼亚美示威期间悬挂俄罗斯国旗。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：萨姆·梅德尼克/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>What is Ecowas and could it reverse the coup?</h3><p> On July 30, 11 countries from the Economic Community of West African States, a political and economic grouping currently led by Nigeria, gave Niger&#39;s junta seven days to reinstate Bazoum, and threatened an armed intervention if it failed to do so. They also imposed a series of tough financial and trade sanctions against Niger in the hope of pressuring the junta to back down.</p><p> In response, Mali and Burkina Faso, whose coups d&#39;état have also been denounced by Ecowas, warned that they would see an armed intervention in Niger as a declaration of war and that they would come to the defense of the junta in Niamey.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-junta-snubs-u-s-backed-peace-mission-a79f76e5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Niger&#39;s military leaders</a> ignored the Ecowas ultimatum and rejected several attempts by Ecowas delegations to negotiate a path toward restoring civilian government in the country.</p><p> On Aug. 10, Nigerian President Bola Tinubu, following a second summit of Ecowas leaders, warned that an armed intervention was still possible if other means of pressuring the junta failed. “No option is taken off the table, including the use of force as a last resort,” Tinubu said. “If we don&#39;t do it, no one else will do it for us.”</p><p> At the summit, Ecowas also ordered the deployment of a “standby force,” but didn&#39;t provide details on the composition of such a force or where and when it would be deployed.</p><p> Analysts warned that an intervention could turn what has until now been a bloodless coup into a regional conflict with many civilian deaths. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          bleed
"><figure class="media-object-image img-bleed"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828965?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> European and US citizens arrived at an airport near Rome after being evacuated from Niger.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: REMO CASILLI/REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3> How is the US responding?</h3><p> President Biden and Secretary of State Antony Blinken have called for Bazoum to be freed and for Niger&#39;s democracy to be protected. On Aug. 4, the administration followed European governments in <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-pause-some-financial-aid-to-niger-as-country-reels-from-coup-7252caa1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">pausing some of its financial assistance</a> to Niger to exert pressure on the junta. Nearly half of Niger&#39;s budget comes from foreign aid, much of it from Western governments.</p><p> However, US officials have been careful to not refer to the military&#39;s actions as a coup, a designation that would trigger <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/state-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-u-s-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">restrictions to military aid</a> under US law.  The Defense Department said it has no plans to move military personnel or equipment out of Niger and supports a diplomatic solution to the situation. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=2AE037D3-6705-43B5-828C-C117387FADDD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fniger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> European governments and the US ordered the evacuation of their citizens from Niger after last week&#39;s coup in the West African country. The leader of the junta said the military won&#39;t bow to pressure to reinstate the ousted president, Mohamed Bazoum. Photo: Sam Mednick/Associated Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>On Aug. 7, acting Deputy Secretary of State Victoria Nuland traveled to Niger and met with one of the junta leaders, Gen.</p> Moussa Salaou Barmou, and his advisers for more than two hours. <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-us-trained-general-65b5ecd6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Barmou once worked</a> very closely with US Special Forces in Niger.<p></p><p> “I hope they will keep the door open to diplomacy. We made that proposal…they have their own ideas about how this goes forward,” Nuland told reporters. “Their ideas do not comport with the constitution and that will be difficult in terms of our relationship if that&#39;s the path that they take. But we gave them a number of options to keep talking and we hope they take us up on it.”</p><p> Several requests to have her meet with Bazoum were denied, she said.</p><p> The State Department has ordered the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/state-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-u-s-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">evacuation of all nonessential personnel</a> from the US Embassy in Niamey, along with family members of American embassy staff. In contrast to France, the US hasn&#39;t launched a full evacuation of American nationals from Niger. France, which has sent several evacuation flights to Niger, said it helped about 40 US citizens leave the country. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828970?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Nigerien President Mohamed Bazoum worked closely with US and European governments to fight Islamist militants.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: REUTERS/Press pool</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3> Who is Gen. Omar Tchiani?</h3><p> Gen. Omar Tchiani,</p> also sometimes called Abdourahamane, was the head of the presidential guard that launched the uprising against Bazoum. He now leads the military junta as Niger&#39;s self-declared leader. Bazoum had been weighing whether to dismiss Tchiani, which was one of the triggers for the coup, according to people familiar with the situation in Niger. <p></p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="390" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-829050?width=700&amp;height=390" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Gen. Omar Tchiani, head of the military junta and Niger&#39;s self-declared leader, led the presidential guard that launched the coup.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: ORTN/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3> What does the Niger junta want?</h3><p> Tchiani and other junta members have cited what they said was Niger&#39;s deteriorating security situation. However, according to data from the nonprofit Armed Conflict Location &amp; Event Data Project, attacks on civilians in Niger declined by 49% in the first half of 2023, while resulting fatalities were down by 16% compared with the previous six months. Last year, there were 114 attacks from jihadist groups in Niger, according to Acled data.</p><p> The junta hasn&#39;t made any public statements about its relations with Moscow, but its early actions suggest that it is likely to pull away from the West. Late on Aug. 3, it announced <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-leaders-end-military-cooperation-with-france-deepening-concerns-over-anti-western-turn-e7fae57e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the end of military cooperation</a> with France, including the authorization for French troops to stay in the country. France&#39;s Foreign Ministry said it doesn&#39;t recognize the junta&#39;s authority and has no plans to withdraw its troops. Tchiani also dispatched one of his deputies to Mali for talks with that country&#39;s pro-Russian leaders.</p><h3> What is Russia&#39;s position on the Niger coup?</h3><p> The Russian government has called for a return to the constitutional order in Niger and warned against an armed intervention. Yevgeny Prigozhin, whose paramilitary Wagner Group already has fighters in Mali, has praised the coup and offered his mercenaries&#39; services to the junta in Niamey.</p><p> France&#39;s foreign minister blamed Russian disinformation for the pro-coup protests that have targeted its embassy.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —William Mauldin and Vivian Salama contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Gabriele Steinhauser at <a href="mailto:Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Gabriele.Steinhauser@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 17:26:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-president-us-fumble-russia-africa-86cf1454-33d18bc<author><![CDATA[Gabriele Steinhauser]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>International Relations</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Omar Tchiani</category><category> Bola Tinubu</category><category> Victoria Nuland</category><category>穆罕默德·巴祖姆</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>military action</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Gulf Nations Poised to Invest Billions in Pakistan]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Islamabad&#39;s powerful military has sought to ease the path for oil-rich monarchies to acquire stakes in mining and energy projects <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124397"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="511" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833144?width=860&amp;height=511" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> &#39;Pakistan is strategically located, at the junction of the engines of growth in Asia,&#39; said Pakistan&#39;s departing planning minister.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Naseem James/Associated Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124397"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/saeed-shah" itemprop="url" rel="author">Saeed Shah</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/summer-said" itemprop="url" rel="author">Summer Said</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 10, 2023 12:26 pm ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/gulf-nations-poised-to-invest-billions-in-pakistan-as-it-seeks-infusion-of-foreign-currency-9dfbb2ad"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> ISLAMABAD, Pakistan—Pakistan is negotiating with Gulf nations to bring in billions of dollars of investment, as Islamabad seeks the foreign currency it <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pakistan-dissolves-parliament-as-government-grapples-with-political-instability-9151fdb2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">badly needs to stabilize its economy</a> and the oil-rich monarchies move to diversify their economies and expand their influence.</p><p> The Saudis are in talks to buy into a copper mine being developed at a cost of $7 billion by Canada&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GOLD" class="company-name">Barrick Gold</a> in western Pakistan, according to people familiar with the project. Separately, negotiations are at an advanced stage to set up a Saudi oil refinery in Pakistan, which could cost up to $14 billion, according to Islamabad and Gulf officials.</p><p> For the Gulf states, the deals represent a shift from when they provided loans or grants to poorer countries in the region, such as Pakistan or Egypt, to a new focus on acquiring assets for their sovereign-wealth funds.</p><p> Pakistan, a nuclear-armed nation of 240 million, has been racked by an economic crisis and political instability. It <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pakistan-clinches-3-billion-in-imf-rescue-lending-698e63ce?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">reached an agreement with the International Monetary Fund</a> in June on another bailout.</p><p> Its powerful military, which has clamped down on political freedoms in recent months, is seeking to ease the path for investment by streamlining the deal-making process for Gulf investors, who had complained about red tape and political indecision in the past.</p><p> Mining, energy infrastructure, farmland and privatizations of Pakistani government businesses could all be part of the planned selloff to Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates and Qatar, which are increasingly competing for assets in struggling political allies. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833146?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Pakistan Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif, hand on chest, met with Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, last year.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: BANDAR ALGALOUD/COURTESY OF SAUD/VIA REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> This summer, Islamabad established the Special Investment Facilitation Council, which includes the army chief, to smooth the bureaucratic path for Gulf investment.</p><p> “Pakistan is strategically located, at the junction of the engines of growth in Asia, between south Asia, central Asia, China and the Middle East,” said Ahsan Iqbal, Pakistan&#39;s departing planning minister, who also heads the executive committee of the Special Investment Facilitation Council. “There is a very big opportunity for investors to come here, as long as we can give them assurance that there will be continuity of policy for their investment.”</p><p> The Saudi deputy mining and foreign ministers visited Islamabad this month for talks about the investment initiative.</p><p> Pakistan Prime Minister Shehbaz Sharif said Wednesday that Parliament would dissolve, ahead of elections that are likely to be delayed into next year. The installment of a nonpolitical caretaker government in Islamabad in the next few days, to oversee the period up to the next election, is expected to kick-start the deals. New powers have been given to the caretaker administration, which will likely be under even greater influence of the military, to enable it to make major economic decisions. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="348" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833673?width=700&amp;height=348" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Pakistan&#39;s army chief, Gen. Asim Munir, visited Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman in Saudi Arabia in January.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Saudi Press Agency/APA Images/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The army is Pakistan&#39;s dominant institution, a permanent power in a country where no prime minister has completed a term in office. The Gulf has long dealt directly with Pakistan&#39;s army, the sixth largest in the world, which has provided a contingent of troops to Saudi Arabia for decades. The first overseas trip for Pakistan&#39;s current army chief, Gen. Asim Munir, was to Saudi Arabia, where he met Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman in January.</p><p> A splurge in Pakistan is expected to come from government-owned entities in the Gulf, which in recent years have invested in Egypt, a country also in the midst of an asset sale, as well as Sudan, Ethiopia and elsewhere in the Horn of Africa.</p><p> “For the Gulf, Pakistan and Egypt are a regional security priority,” said Karen E. Young, a researcher at Columbia University&#39;s Center on Global Energy Policy. “They absolutely cannot afford to see a failed state in Egypt or Pakistan.”</p><p> Egypt and Pakistan offer big populations, large tracts of arable land and huge armies, all attributes lacking in the Gulf, said Faisal Aftab, founder of Pakistan-based Zayn Venture Capital.</p><p> “This is a last chance for Pakistan,” said Aftab. “It needs to leverage in investment.”</p><p> Iqbal, the planning minister, said Pakistan was hoping for deals worth around $25 billion, including in solar energy and information technology. Pakistan&#39;s defense industries are also open for investment, and the country is prepared to offer uncultivated government land on long leases for agriculture.</p><p> The Gulf nations haven&#39;t put figures in recent weeks on how much they might spend. In January this year, the Saudis said they were willing <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/saudi-arabia-signals-it-could-provide-pakistan-an-11-billion-lifeline-11673374626?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to invest $10 billion</a> , after Pakistan&#39;s army chief visited. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="422" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833157?width=700&amp;height=422" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Islamabad is looking for investors to take on its national carrier, Pakistan International Airlines.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: faisal mahmood/Reuters</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Economic crises in Egypt and Pakistan, which have been buffeted by higher fuel and food prices from the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-uses-small-unit-tactics-to-retake-captured-territory-from-russia-d9ef32a3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Russia-Ukraine war</a> and seen their currencies plummet, mean that assets are potentially available on the cheap. But Riyadh has still balked at prices in Egypt, meaning fewer deals than anticipated have materialized so far. Pakistan will also have to manage competition between Gulf nations for assets, already being felt, especially between Saudi Arabia and UAE, which <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/frenemies-saudi-crown-prince-mbs-clashes-uae-president-mbz-c500f9b1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">have strained relations</a> .</p><p> Among the first contracts likely to attract interest, from both UAE and Qatar, is a tender announced this week, by open bidding, to run terminal services at Islamabad airport. The two Gulf countries fiercely competed for the contract to run Kabul airport in Pakistan&#39;s neighbor Afghanistan, a contest won last year by the UAE Islamabad is also looking for investors to take on its national carrier, Pakistan International Airlines.</p><p> Musadik Malik, Pakistan&#39;s departing petroleum minister, said that a deal for a Saudi refinery was “very close.” Saudi Aramco, the company named by Pakistani officials as its partner for the project, declined to comment. The refinery would likely be located at Gwadar, the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-pakistan-attacks-belt-and-road-11669218179?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">port developed by China</a> on the Arabian Sea, and the centerpiece of Beijing&#39;s investment program in ally Pakistan. Riyadh is moving closer to Beijing, at the expense of its relationship with Washington. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="440" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833148?width=700&amp;height=440" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Saudi Arabian Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman on a trip to Islamabad several years ago. In January this year, the Saudis said they were willing to invest $10 billion, after Pakistan&#39;s army chief visited the kingdom.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: handout/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Officials from both sides are aiming for a final deal on the refinery—which would be the country&#39;s biggest—by the end of this year, with construction to begin early in 2024.</p><p> Malik said that he anticipated a series of mining deals that would be much bigger in value than the refinery contract.</p><p> “We have enormous untapped resources just sitting there,” he said.</p><p> The obvious prize is copper, a metal needed in the transition to cleaner energy. One of the world&#39;s biggest new copper mines is expected to begin production in 2028. The <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/pakistan-reaches-deal-with-mining-companies-11647793113?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Reko Diq mine</a> is a joint venture between Barrick Gold and the government of Pakistan, in a remote part of the country hit by two violent insurgencies.</p><p> Talks are under way for the Saudis to buy into the Reko Diq mine. The Saudi sovereign-wealth fund, Public Investment Fund, would team up with Saudi mining company Ma&#39;aden, to acquire part of the 50% stake in the mine owned by Pakistan, according to people involved. In addition, the Saudis could be given exploration rights in other parts of the copper-rich area.</p><p> Riyadh has ambitions to turn Ma&#39;aden into a global company, but it is wary of the security risks at the Pakistani mine. In July, Saudi Arabia <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/vale-nears-deal-to-sell-10-of-its-base-metals-business-to-saudi-arabia-3acba3f7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">said it would buy a $2.5 billion stake</a> in Brazilian mining company <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/VALE" class="">Vale</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> also through the same fund and Ma&#39;aden.</p><p> For Islamabad, there are strategic advantages to tying Saudi Arabia in, while Barrick has joined with Saudi Arabia elsewhere too. Barrick and Ma&#39;aden didn&#39;t respond to requests for comment. The Public Investment Fund declined to comment.</p><p> The Saudis are the most interested in the mining opportunities, say officials and experts, while the UAE is looking most keenly at agriculture, clean energy and logistics.</p><p> Just ahead of the launch of the Gulf initiative, the UAE swooped in early, acquiring a 50-year lease in June to operate part of the container terminal at Karachi port. The financial terms weren&#39;t disclosed for the deal, which was awarded without an open bidding process. Many coming transactions are also not expected to involve competitive bidding, Pakistani officials say. That approach could open the divestments up to domestic controversy.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Rory Jones contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Saeed Shah at <a href="mailto:saeed.shah@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">saeed.shah@wsj.com</a> and Summer Said at <a href="mailto:summer.said@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">summer.said@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 16:26:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/gulf-nations-poised-to-invest-billions-in-pakistan-as-it-seeks-infusion-of-foreign-currency-9dfbb2ad</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/gulf-nations-poised-to-invest-billions-in-pakistan-as-it-seeks-infusion-of-foreign-currency-9dfbb2ad<author><![CDATA[Saeed ShahSummer Said]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>活力</category><category>金属矿石开采</category><category>Copper Ore/Nickel Ore Mining</category><category>基本材料/资源</category><category>Gold Ore Mining</category><category>采矿/采石</category><category>有色金属矿开采</category><category>容量/设施</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>Natural Reserves/Resources Discovery</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>Energy Security</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>Money/Currency Markets</category><category> Foreign Exchange Markets</category><category> Commodity/Financial Market News</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Barrick Gold</category><category> ABX.T</category><category> CA:ABX</category><category>容量</category><category>设施</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>natural reserves</category><category> resources discovery</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>energy security</category><category>政治</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>钱</category><category>currency markets</category><category> foreign exchange markets</category><category>商品</category><category>financial market news</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>活力</category><category>金属矿石开采</category><category>copper ore</category><category> nickel ore mining</category><category>基础材料</category><category>资源</category><category>gold ore mining</category><category>矿业</category><category>采石</category><category>有色金属矿开采</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Investment Ban on China Poised to Deepen Divide]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>拜登总统的命令是在中国经济放缓、新冠疫情封锁以及两国之间紧张关系加剧的背景下发布的<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833088?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：POOL/来自路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001123931"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/charles-hutzler" itemprop="url" rel="author">查尔斯·赫茨勒</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">Updated Aug. 10, 2023 11:54 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>华盛顿——经过多年将中国企业列入黑名单并审查它们在美国的投资，拜登政府<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">正在向美国企业发出明确的信号</a>，要求其将投资从中国转移出去。</p><p> An executive order President Biden issued Wednesday—while narrowly targeted at critical leading-edge technologies with military, surveillance and cyber capabilities—more broadly aims to reorder the flow of American capital and expertise away from <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-allies-could-counter-chinas-economic-coercionif-they-unite-c45d2f8d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">its biggest global rival</a> .</p><p>该命令禁止美国投资<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-u-s-uses-supply-chain-sway-to-throttle-chinas-chip-development-11666526403?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">先进半导体</a>和量子计算，并要求美国投资者就其他类型半导体和人工智能的投资通知华盛顿。它还禁止美国公民和永久居民参与违禁交易。</p><p>白宫官员表示，该命令旨在剥夺中国获得美国风险投资和私募股权公司投资带来的技术诀窍、市场准入和其他好处。除了中国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-slips-into-deflation-in-warning-sign-for-world-economy-bbefb179" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济增长疲软</a>、新冠疫情封锁导致前往中国变得困难，以及最近在华盛顿和北京之间紧张局势加剧之际，针对美国和其他外国公司的施压行动，这可能会进一步扰乱在中国开展业务的美国公司。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833086?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登总统的命令针对的是具有军事、监视和网络能力的关键前沿技术。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>精品研究公司Trivium China的合伙人安德鲁·波尔克(Andrew Polk)表示，虽然他所建议的美国公司仍然对中国市场感兴趣，但许多公司已经变得犹豫不决。</p><p> “我们总是说——这引起了我们客户的共鸣——中国的风险调整回报已经发生了巨大变化，”波尔克说。 “所以我们看到很多公司从根本上重新思考他们的中国战略。这并不意味着他们一定会改变它们，但他们现在正在对它们进行压力测试，因为我们显然处于一个新环境中。”</p><p>周三的命令是在华盛顿和北京在台湾、乌克兰战争、间谍活动和技术控制等问题上经历了数月的严重紧张关系之后，正处于脆弱的关系之中。 In the short term, officials and security specialists said, the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/janet-yellen-says-u-s-china-making-progress-on-managing-economic-tensions-1e2c07?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">tentative diplomatic progress</a> of recent months is likely to hold.</p><p>中国领导人习近平认为，在经济陷入通货紧缩<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sputtering-trade-fuels-fears-for-a-connected-world-81c99922?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">、增长放缓和外国投资大幅下降之际，</a>与美国关系的平静（至少是暂时的）可以提升他在国内的威望。中国外交部高级官员杨涛上周在华盛顿与国务院和其他官员进行了讨论，重点是为习近平出席11月在旧金山举行的亚太领导人峰会以及与拜登举行单独会谈做准备据了解讨论情况的人士透露。</p><p>官员们表示，双方还推动修复沟通渠道，本月初步同意成立工作组来讨论亚太地区和海事问题。目前仍在讨论商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多（Gina Raimondo）是否可能在本月晚些时候访问北京，这将是拜登政府高级官员自 6 月以来第四次访问北京。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=607DAEAC-FDF3-4309-B753-4A08C846B405&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-and-china-poised-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">从喷气式飞机到电动汽车再到超级计算机，《华尔街日报》与不同的行业和技术专家讨论了两国在设计、工程和战略方面的匹配情况。照片插图：迈克尔·塔布和盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>然而，从长远来看，美国和中国陷入竞争，迫使两国割裂数十年来稳定两国关系的经济和商业联系，而新的投资限制可能会加速两国进一步分裂的势头。</p><p> “关于多元化、去风险、脱钩、解开的言论——选择你的‘D字’，无论你喜欢哪个——它确实已经深入华盛顿的头脑，越来越多地在硅谷，而且这确实是在华尔街传播的前国家安全委员会官员丽莎·托宾 (Liza Tobin) 表示，她目前在华盛顿的一个专门研究技术政策的组织“特别竞争研究项目”工作。</p><p>曾经大力涌入中国的风险投资公司已经退出，部分原因是紧张局势加剧； Crunchbase 的数据显示，从 2021 年到 2022 年，美国对中国初创企业的投资下降了 30% 以上，今年还将进一步下降。</p><p>例如，据一位知情人士透露，总部位于加利福尼亚州的风险投资公司 Lightspeed Venture Partners 于 2006 年成立了中国分部，由于风险原因，该公司已削减了对中国初创企业的投资。</p><p>保卫民主基金会研究员、供应链情报公司 Horizo​​n Advisory 联合创始人内特·皮卡西克 (Nate Picarsic) 表示，“这一举措传达的真正信息是，这是一条持久的轨迹”，公司和投资者必须考虑这一点。 “地缘政治和国家安全风险已成为永久性的问题。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833087?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">随着中国从疫情中恢复过来，今年的经济增长出现了放缓。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：TINGSHU WANG/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>随着近几个月行政命令的形成，中国官员敦促美国不要通过该命令，并指责华盛顿试图阻碍中国的发展。 After the order&#39;s unveiling, China&#39;s foreign ministry on Thursday deplored the move and said Biden was backtracking on past statements that the US isn&#39;t looking to decouple economically.</p><p> “This is deglobalization and a move to phase China out,” a foreign ministry statement said. It urged the US to “stop politicizing, instrumentalizing and weaponizing tech and trade issues, immediately cancel the wrong decisions, remove the restrictions on investments in China” and improve the environment for business cooperation.</p><p>过去十年中，在习近平政府制定了主导尖端行业的计划，并加大了对外国公司转让专有技术的压力后，有关技术和市场准入的争端已酝酿多年，并在过去十年中爆发为更加激烈的冲突。</p><p>特朗普政府将中国军方供应商列入黑名单并加强对中国在美投资的审查，随后拜登政府又全面禁止先进半导体及其制造设备的转让以及美国公民和永久居民的参与在那个部门。美国还让盟友日本和荷兰效仿。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-bans-micron-as-supplier-to-big-chinese-firms-citing-national-security-5f326b90?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国进行了报复</a>，对对绿色技术至关重要的矿物出口实施管制，并禁止美国芯片制造商<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MU" class="company-name">美光科技</a>在关键基础设施中使用产品。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为中美关系将走向何方？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>财政部长珍妮特·耶伦上个月访问北京时试图缓解中国对当时正在讨论的投资限制的担忧，并阻止报复。她说，她解释说，这些措施的目的是缩小范围，是为了国家安全目的，而不是为了经济优势，她预计北京也会这样做。</p><p> “国家安全是我们不能妥协的事情，我们会保护它，即使这会损害我们自己狭隘的经济利益，我们也会这样做。但当我们采取这些确实对中国经济产生影响的行动时，我们将确保这些行动是透明的、目标明确的、解释清楚的，”耶伦上个月在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PARA" class="">哥伦比亚广播</a><span class="company-name-type">公司的</span>“面对国家”节目中表示。 ”</p><p> “我要指出的是，中国也通过出口管制和其他类似手段保护自己的国家安全，”耶伦说。</p><p> The Chinese foreign ministry statement suggested possible retaliation, saying Beijing will “resolutely safeguard our rights and interests.”如果北京这样做，它可能会谨慎选择，以避免损害本国企业并进一步削弱经济。</p><p>其中一个特别的弱点是电动汽车和太阳能技术，中国在这两个领域的供应链中占据主导地位。保卫民主基金会的皮卡西克表示，他认为投资限制会蔓延开来，影响美国投资者进入其他领域的意愿，特别是生物技术等可以增强军事或警察能力的领域。</p><p> “这里的结构性基本面是竞争和升级，我认为到目前为止，从美国政府围绕这一举措发出的信号、中国的期望和潜在反应来看，我们所看到的任何事情都表明没有任何突破。 ，“ 他说。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Berber Jin、Lingling Wei 和 Vivian Salama 对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给查尔斯·赫兹勒 (Charles Hutzler)： <a href="mailto:charles.hutzler@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">charles.hutzler@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:54:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-and-china-poished-to-drift-further-apart-after-investment-ban-1e37427d<author><![CDATA[Charles Hutzler]]></author><category>华尔街日报华盛顿</category><category>华尔街日报</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>International Relations</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>疫情/流行病</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>呼吸道疾病</category><category>国际关系</category><category>健康</category><category>医疗条件</category><category>爆发</category><category>流行病</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>新型冠状病毒</category><category>传染性疾病</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Ukraine Offers Plan to Bypass Russia’s Black Sea Blockade]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Russia and Ukraine have been threatening shipping routes in the crucial waterway <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124890"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-833318?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Ships at the grain terminal at the port in Odesa, southern Ukraine.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Ritzau Scanpix/Zuma Press </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001124890"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/jared-malsin" itemprop="url" rel="author">Jared Malsin</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/anastasiia-malenko" itemprop="url" rel="author">Anastasiia Malenko</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 10, 2023 11:01 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offers-plan-to-bypass-russias-black-sea-blockade-fcac8ef"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Ukraine said it was opening temporary routes for civilian ships to sail from its Black Sea ports in a potential challenge to Russia&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-threats-to-shipping-bring-risk-of-war-to-black-sea-247cbf3a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">attempt to blockade</a> the country&#39;s globally important food exports.</p><p> The new routes would primarily be used to open an exit route for ships that have been trapped in Ukraine&#39;s ports since Russia&#39;s full-scale invasion in February 2022, the Ukrainian navy said in a statement.</p><p> The navy also said that “throughout all routes there is a military threat and mine danger from the Russian Federation.” Any vessels whose owners or captains said they are ready to sail in these conditions could pass to or from three ports around the city of Odesa, it added.</p><p> It remains unclear if any commercial shipowners, insurers and ship captains will participate in the plan.</p><p> “No one is forcing anyone to do this. It is completely voluntary,” said navy spokesman Oleh Chalyk, when asked whether the vessels would make use of the corridor. “Ukraine was forced to make this decision and provide this route. The corridor was closed and we found one way out of this situation.”</p><p> All commercial shipping to Ukraine&#39;s major Black Sea ports <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-strikes-odesa-port-after-quitting-black-sea-grain-deal-4df967bd?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">ceased last month</a> after Russia withdrew from an international agreement that guaranteed the safety of ships carrying grain and other food products from Ukraine.</p><p> Russia has since <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/great-power-rivalry-looms-over-ukraine-grain-deal-3d2e0eb1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">threatened to attack commercial vessels</a> heading to Ukraine and launched a series of missile and drone attacks on key Ukrainian ports and grain infrastructure, driving up the price of wheat and renewing concerns that the invasion will threaten global food security.</p><p> Some commercial ships have remained trapped in Ukrainian ports since the invasion began and have lost all but a skeleton crew.</p><p> Moving any ships out of Ukraine&#39;s ports would be a challenge to Russia&#39;s threats to interdict vessels in the Black Sea, industry experts said.</p><p> “Ironically it might be a good way to test the Russian ability or resolve as I guess most of these vessels are empty,” said Jonathan Grange, a partner at Sunstone Brokers, an agricultural-commodities brokerage working in Ukraine and the Black Sea region.</p><p> Since Russia reimposed its de facto blockade of the largest Ukrainian ports, Ukraine has pushed back in other ways, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukrainian-sea-drones-attack-russian-oil-tanker-in-black-sea-dfa07364?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">launching attacks using maritime drones</a> on a Russian warship and a bridge linking Russia to the occupied Crimean Peninsula. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F461056A-8654-4C46-8FE3-867860EC96B9&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fukraine-offers-plan-to-bypass-russias-black-sea-blockade-fcac8ef&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> A Ukrainian naval drone hit a Russian oil tanker in the Kerch Strait near Crimea, Russian state media reported on Saturday. Photo: Ukrainian Military via Storyful<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>“The Ukrainian Navy&#39;s decision to protect vessels closer to the Ukrainian coastline comes after Ukraine&#39;s recent demonstrations of longer-range capabilities, including drones, demonstrating both defense and offensive capabilities in the maritime domain. Ukraine has vowed to fight back against Russia, and Ukraine is good for its word,” said Thea Dunlevie, a senior analyst at the Center for Maritime Strategy, a think tank in the Washington area.</p><p> Ukraine has also threatened ships heading to Russian ports and declared a “war risk” area along Russia&#39;s Black Sea coast in what military experts say is an attempt to freeze out some commercial shipping from the area.</p><p> Turkish and United Nations officials are working to prod Russia to rejoin the grain agreement, in which Ukraine was allowed to reopen three of its major Black Sea ports for grain exports in an agreement that lowered global food prices.</p><p> Ukraine, which is one of the world&#39;s largest exporters of wheat, corn and sunflower oil, exported more than 32 million tons of food under the agreement, in which Russian, Turkish, Ukrainian and UN officials worked together to guide ships along a designated maritime corridor.</p><p> The public will be able to monitor the vessels that decide to participate through a broadcast, officials say. The livestream would guarantee that “these vessels do not create any military threats,” said Chalyk. Ukraine began issuing the coastal warning about the opening of the corridor earlier today and the vessels will travel shortly, he added.</p><p> Since the deal unraveled in July, Ukraine has continued to export grain overland and on smaller boats via the Danube River. Turkish and UN officials are under pressure to negotiate a resumption of the deal by September when Ukraine&#39;s grain harvest will begin to pile up, creating a backlog that could be difficult to export.</p><p> Write to Jared Malsin at <a href="mailto:jared.malsin@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">jared.malsin@wsj.com</a> and Anastasiia Malenko at <a href="mailto:anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">anastasiia.malenko@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 10 Aug 2023 15:01:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offers-plan-to-bypass-russias-black-sea-blockade-fcac8ef</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-offers-plan-to-bypass-russias-black-sea-blockade-fcac8ef<author><![CDATA[Jared MalsinAnastasiia Malenko]]></author><category> ukraine</category><category> Inland Water Transport</category><category> Port/Harbor Operations</category><category> Water Transport/Shipping</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>International Relations</category><category> Navy</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>国际关系</category><category>navy</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>military action</category><category> inland water transport</category><category>港口</category><category>harbor operations</category><category> water transport</category><category>船运</category><category>运输</category><category>后勤</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Robert F. Kennedy Jr.’s Unsubstantiated Bioweapon Claims Find Audience in China]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Beijing uses statements from long-shot presidential candidate known for advancing conspiracy theories to bolster its own talking points <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001110254"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-827454?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> In the US, Democratic presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr.&#39;s comments have been widely criticized as racist and antisemitic.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: AMR ALFIKY/REUTERS </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001110254"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/natasha-khan" itemprop="url" rel="author">Natasha Khan</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/clarence-leong" itemprop="url" rel="author">Clarence Leong</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 10, 2023 10:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-f-kennedy-jr-s-unsubstantiated-bioweapon-claims-find-big-audience-in-china-61472bab"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> HONG KONG—As China&#39;s media outlets cover the early stages of the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/presidential-election-2024-candidates-dates-guide-a264d4fe?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">US presidential campaign</a> , much of the Chinese public is getting a vastly different view of the race, one that is filtered through the lens of the Communist Party&#39;s propaganda.</p><p> Take, for example, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-f-kennedy-election-presidential-campaign-2024-5265d2b8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">recent comments</a> by long-shot Democratic candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr., who claimed the US was collecting Russian and Chinese DNA “so we can target people by race” with “ethnic bioweapons.” He said that Covid-19 had been designed to target Caucasians and Black people and that the people who are “most immune are Ashkenazi Jews and Chinese people.”</p><p> Kennedy&#39;s comments were widely criticized as racist and antisemitic in the US, including by his fellow Democrats. Scientists dismissed his claims about bioweapons, saying that human genetic variations exist along a continuum and no hard line can be drawn to distinguish one ethnic or population group from another based on DNA.</p><p> His comments about bioweapons found a big audience in China, where they were fanned by media outlets backed by the Communist Party.</p><p> The Communist Youth League jumped on the remarks, posting video of Kennedy speaking on the popular Weibo social-media platform. It was quickly amplified by the accounts of several party-linked media outlets, using the hashtag “#US Presidential Candidate Says US Is Collecting Chinese DNA.”</p><p> In the weeks since Kennedy made the remarks, the hashtag has attracted 230 million views. On the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TCEHY" class="company-name">WeChat</a> microblogging platform, a video of Kennedy&#39;s remarks posted on an account affiliated with China&#39;s National Defense News was shared more than 100,000 times. The same day Kennedy <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/robert-f-kennedy-jr-antisemitism-house-hearing-censorship-8ba7e519?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">testified before Congress last month</a> , he rose to the No. 2 trending topic on Weibo.</p><p> Neither the Youth League nor any of the other party-linked social-media accounts that repeated Kennedy&#39;s bioweapon comments offered context from scientists or seriously challenged his assertions.</p><p> In a statement to The Wall Street Journal, the Kennedy campaign said he looks forward to building peaceful relationships with the Chinese government and getting rid of all weapons that threaten humanity. China&#39;s State Council Information Office and the US State Department didn&#39;t reply to requests for comment.</p><p> The episode illustrated how Chinese media is primed to pick up selectively on comments that serve to reinforce the Communist Party&#39;s talking points, with the US presidential race playing out against a backdrop of <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-ban-some-investments-in-china-71f519d6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">historically high tensions</a> between Washington and Beijing. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828041?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Communist Youth League jumped on remarks made in the run-up to the US presidential election.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Yan Yan/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> The Communist Youth League and China&#39;s state media “will use all means at their disposal, including quoting senior US figures, to discredit the US and enlist wide public support in the existential competition against the USA,” said Steve Tsang, director of the China Institute at the School of Oriental and African Studies in London.</p><p> Chinese state media also recently seized on remarks from Democrat Marianne Williamson. When asked about how she would respond to China&#39;s negotiations with Cuba over <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-plans-a-new-training-facility-in-cuba-raising-prospect-of-chinese-troops-on-americas-doorstep-e17fd5d1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">setting up a joint military-training base</a> , she pointed out that China is surrounded by American military bases. Williamson, like Kennedy, is seen as unlikely to seriously challenge President Biden for the Democratic nomination.</p><p> After leading Republican candidate and former President <a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a> was <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-indictment-jack-smith-2020-election-4b351abf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">indicted on criminal charges</a> in connection with his attempts to stay in power after losing the 2020 election, the Youth League&#39;s flagship newspaper China Youth Daily said it showed that “American society will continue to be trapped in the vortex of deep division, unable to extricate itself.”</p><p> As the US election season approaches, Chinese propaganda wants to show that “this is a very bad example of elections and try to emphasize the beauty of authoritarian rule,” said Alfred Wu, an associate professor at National University of Singapore who studies public governance in China.</p><p> The comments about bioweapons by Kennedy came from a recent campaign event at a New York City restaurant and were captured on video by the New York Post. After his remarks were criticized, Kennedy pointed to a 2020 study that said a receptor for the virus appeared not to be present in Amish people or Ashkenazi Jews. The study didn&#39;t mention Chinese people or attempt to make a case that the virus was designed to target certain groups of people.</p><p> Experts have said science doesn&#39;t support his claims about bioweapons. Even if there were a way to target a genetic variation that exists at a more extreme frequency in a certain population of people, it would still have only a preferential, but not exclusive, effect on that group, said Anthony J. Brookes, a professor of genomics and data science at the University of Leicester.</p><p> White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre</p> described Kennedy&#39;s suggestion that Covid-19 had been targeted at particular groups of people as racist and antisemitic, calling it “an attack on our fellow citizens, our fellow Americans.”<p></p><p> Claims and counterclaims about the origin of Covid-19 have fueled debate in the scientific and intelligence communities throughout the pandemic, often fueling online speculation. Parts of the US government, including the Federal Bureau of Investigation and the Energy Department, have concluded that the Covid-19 pandemic most likely resulted from an <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-origin-china-lab-leak-807b7b0a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">unintended lab leak in China</a> , although other agencies maintain that it was caused by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/covid-virus-wasnt-at-wuhan-lab-before-pandemic-u-s-report-says-da8511c8?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">natural transmission from an infected animal</a> .</p><p> In response to the World Health Organization&#39;s calls to further investigate the possibility of a lab leak, China said the WHO should also look at evidence of early outbreaks in other countries and suggested the probes of laboratories should include the <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-says-covid-19-origin-probe-should-shift-focus-to-other-countries-11617186625?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">US military laboratory at Fort Detrick, Md.</a></p><p> China&#39;s propaganda apparatus has consistently leveraged online conspiracy theories to serve its aims, said Renée DiResta, research manager at Stanford University&#39;s Internet Observatory.</p><p> “Creating doubt and excusing culpability by blaming an enemy are tried-and-true propaganda strategies,” DiResta said, “and so is leveraging local purported &#39;whistleblowers&#39; to make the allegations more credible.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828042?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Robert F. Kennedy Jr. arrives last month to testify at a US House committee hearing.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Julia Nikhinson/Cnp/dpa/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Write to Natasha Khan at <a href="mailto:natasha.khan@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">natasha.khan@wsj.com</a> and Clarence Leong at <a href="mailto:clarence.leong@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">clarence.leong@wsj.com</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web
